=================================================
SELENIUM GRID WITH DOCKER - QUICK REFERENCE
=================================================

1. Pull Images
-------------------------------------------------

docker pull selenium/hub

docker pull selenium/node-chrome

docker pull selenium/node-edge


2. Verify Downloaded Images
-------------------------------------------------

docker images


3. Create Docker Network
-------------------------------------------------

docker network create grid


4. Create Selenium Hub Container
-------------------------------------------------

docker run -d --name selenium-hub --network grid -p 4442:4442 -p 4443:4443 -p 4444:4444 selenium/hub


5. Create Chrome Node Container
-------------------------------------------------

docker run -d --name chrome-node --network grid -e SE_EVENT_BUS_HOST=selenium-hub -e SE_EVENT_BUS_PUBLISH_PORT=4442 -e SE_EVENT_BUS_SUBSCRIBE_PORT=4443 selenium/node-chrome


6. Create Edge Node Container
-------------------------------------------------

docker run -d --name edge-node --network grid -e SE_EVENT_BUS_HOST=selenium-hub -e SE_EVENT_BUS_PUBLISH_PORT=4442 -e SE_EVENT_BUS_SUBSCRIBE_PORT=4443 selenium/node-edge


7. Verify Running Containers
-------------------------------------------------

docker ps


8. Verify Docker Network
-------------------------------------------------

docker network ls

docker network inspect grid


9. Open Selenium Grid UI
-------------------------------------------------

http://localhost:4444


10. View Container Logs
-------------------------------------------------

docker logs selenium-hub

docker logs chrome-node

docker logs edge-node


11. Enter a Container
-------------------------------------------------

docker exec -it chrome-node bash

docker exec -it edge-node bash


12. Check Linux OS Inside Container
-------------------------------------------------

uname -a


13. Stop Containers
-------------------------------------------------

docker stop selenium-hub chrome-node edge-node


14. Start Containers Again
-------------------------------------------------

docker start selenium-hub chrome-node edge-node


15. Remove Containers
-------------------------------------------------

docker rm -f selenium-hub chrome-node edge-node


16. Remove Network
-------------------------------------------------

docker network rm grid


IMPORTANT NOTES
-------------------------------------------------

1. Selenium Docker images are Linux-based containers.

2. Hub is the central server that manages nodes.

3. Chrome Node and Edge Node register themselves with the Hub.

4. Selenium tests connect to:
   http://localhost:4444

5. Docker Containers ≠ Virtual Machines.

6. Architecture:

   Windows Laptop
        |
     Docker
        |
     Network (grid)
        |
   ---------------------
   |         |         |
   Hub    Chrome    Edge
          Node      Node

7. Verify Grid Status:
   Open http://localhost:4444
   You should see:
   - 1 Chrome Node
   - 1 Edge Node

